
// Replaces occurrences of the specified string within another string with a new string. The slot takes two arguments: the first specifies the string to be replaced, and the second specifies the replacement string. In this example, it replaces all instances of a newline character with the string "\n" in the value of the [description] node.
strings.replace:x:@.arguments/*/description
   .:@"
"
   .:"\n"
